{"body": "Yeah, I suppose that would work. It just seems like it's really close to what the pluralize method is already doing.\r\n\r\nI guess I'm confused about the criteria for accepting the feature into Rails. @pixeltrix mentioned that it was an application-level concern, but it seems to me like it's a natural extension of the pluralize helper that's already in Rails. What's the criteria for making that decision?\r\n\r\nThanks for your help.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/13418699", "created_at": "2013-02-12T05:24:37Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5490#issuecomment-13418699", "updated_at": "2013-02-12T05:24:37Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5490, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/graysonwright/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/graysonwright/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/graysonwright/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/graysonwright", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/graysonwright/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/graysonwright", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/graysonwright/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/6a2e183a609cf77e2b7078bd6767f262?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fae21d010843a977b79afc76bbed88b3c.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/graysonwright/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/graysonwright/received_events", "gravatar_id": "6a2e183a609cf77e2b7078bd6767f262", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/graysonwright/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "graysonwright", "type": "User", "id": 829576, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/graysonwright/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523ebd11bd354364b901265d"}, "id": 13418699, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5490"}
